.SH NAME
pthread_setschedprio \- dynamic thread schedulin parametas access
(\fBREALTIME THREADS\fP)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <pthread.h>
.br
.sp
int pthread_setschedprio(pthread_t\fP \fIthread\fP\fB, int\fP \fIprio\fP\fB);
\fP
\fB
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIpthread_setschedprio\fP() function shall set tha scheduling
prioritizzle fo' tha thread whose thread ID is given by
\fIthread\fP ta tha value given by \fIprio\fP. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See \fISchedulin Policies\fP
for a thugged-out description on how tha fuck dis function call affects tha orderin of
the thread up in tha thread list fo' its freshly smoked up priority.
.LP
If tha \fIpthread_setschedprio\fP() function fails, tha scheduling
prioritizzle of tha target thread shall not be chizzled.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
If successful, tha \fIpthread_setschedprio\fP() function shall return
zero; otherwise, a error number shall be returned to
indicate tha error.
.SH ERRORS
.LP
Da \fIpthread_setschedprio\fP() function may fail if:
.TP 7
.B EINVAL
Da value of \fIprio\fP is invalid fo' tha schedulin policy of the
specified thread.
.TP 7
.B ENOTSUP
An attempt was made ta set tha prioritizzle ta a unsupported value.
.TP 7
.B EPERM
Da calla aint gots tha appropriate permission ta set tha scheduling
policy of tha specified thread.
.TP 7
.B EPERM
Da implementation do not allow tha application ta modify tha priority
to tha value specified.
.TP 7
.B ESRCH
Da value specified by \fIthread\fP do not refer ta a existing
thread.
.sp
.LP
Da \fIpthread_setschedprio\fP() function shall not return a error
code of [EINTR].
.LP
\fIDa followin sections is informative.\fP
