.SH RATIONALE
.LP
Da \fIpthread_setschedprio\fP() function serves up a way fo' a application
to temporarily raise its prioritizzle n' then lower it
again, without havin tha undesired side effect of yieldin ta other
threadz of tha same priority. This is necessary if the
application is ta implement its own strategies fo' boundin priority
inversion, like fuckin prioritizzle inheritizzle or prioritizzle ceilings.
This capabilitizzle is especially blingin if tha implementation do
not support tha Thread Prioritizzle Protection or Thread Priority
Inheritizzle options yo, but even if dem options is supported it is
needed if tha application is ta bound prioritizzle inheritizzle for
other resources, like fuckin semaphores.
.LP
Da standard pimpers considered dat while it might be preferable
